\begin_layout Section
Barra Velha Formation and Lacustrine Depositional Environment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
According to 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "amorim2021analise"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, the Barra Velha Formation, located in the Santos Basin and dated to the
 Aptian age, originated in a lacustrine environment and consists of carbonate
 deposits from the 'Pre-Salt' petroleum play.
 This formation is of interest due to various uncertainties related to its
 evolution, the microbial influence on rock diagenesis, and the type of
 depositional environment.
 Additionally, carbonates, by their very nature, exhibit significant heterogenei
ties, as do the associated minerals found in this formation, indicating
 specific conditions for their formation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Barra Velha Formation has its base marked by the Pré-Alagoas unconformity,
 which separates it from the bioclastic deposits and shales of the Itapema
 Formation, as observed by Chinelatto et al.
