 and African continents, genetically related deposits to the Barra Velha
 Formation, such as the Macabú Formation in the Campos Basin (Herlinguer
 et al., 2017), and the sag phase deposits of the West African basins (Kwanza
 Basin, Saller et al., 2016), can be integrated to understand the predominant
 depositional system during the Aptian and the sedimentary and diagenetic
 processes that affected the Pre-Salt reservoirs.
\end_layout

